<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Lutz</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-04 05:57:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Got this item recently, heres the scoop.<BR>
<BR>
Boondin Babbinshort spawns on the 3rd floor. ok. Lemme try and explain this.<BR>
<BR>
You know the fake wall that you can go through, that leads to where the BBC and the gossimer drop? Theres a chair right in there? Well, face that wall, and turn around, face the other way. Theres a door. Go in, go in the other door. Boondin spawns behind the biggest rock in the room. I only had to wait a good 20 minutes for him to spawn.<BR>
<BR>
Alright, heres the really wierd part.<BR>
<BR>
There were 2 other necro NPCs in the room, an erudite theurgist, and a human acolyte. As SOON as Boondin popped, the other two necros attacked him. Wierd eh? Has this happened to anyone else?<BR>
<BR>
That, and Boondin conned warmly to me. (L39 Druid).<BR>
<BR>
Go figure.</font></td></tr></table>
